text: Nils-Erik Haglund (19 June 1893 - 19 March 1921) was a Swedish swimmer. He competed in the men's 400 metre freestyle event at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1921 deaths Category:Swedish male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Sweden Category:Swimmers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Stockholm
